                <m>\cos(y^3)</m> over the region <m>D</m> is
                <me>
                  \frac{I}{\text{ Area } (D)} = \frac{\frac{\sin(8)}{3}}{\frac{8}{3}} = \frac{1}{8}\sin(8)
                </me>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </solution>

        
